# Leacme.Objectiv

**Leacme Objectiv** is a cross-platform application that is currently targeted for mobile devices. It is build using the [Godot Engine](https://github.com/godotengine/godot).

This application features the ability to view the model meshes stored in .obj files.

![][image_screenshot]

## Application Compiling

The application can be compiled into the platform-specific executable with the Godot Engine via the following [instructions](https://docs.godotengine.org/en/latest/getting_started/workflow/export/index.html). Make sure to run `nuget restore` to fetch dependencies specified in the .csproj file prior to building with Godot.

## Application Usage

Click the "Open .obj" button to load one of the preset meshes from file. Drag finger on screen to rotate model.
